Flaco's is a rare gem in Washington Heights. Gentrification in The Heightz has eradicated many local shops in the area. The fact that Flaco's Pizzeria is still open and serving the community speaks volumes on how the charm of this quaint establishment can survive in a climate where gentrification has caused many local, mom and pop stores to close their doors. A round of applause to El Flaco where with each bite of his pizza one can discern how much love and heart he puts into it.

This is our local 'do the minimum' pizza.  If you're looking for no frills bread sauce and cheese you have come to the right place.  The best thing I can say about this place is that since there aren't any good options in the neighborhood, this is what you get when you really need a slice (and sometimes you do.)  They are expensive what ti is, they don't stand out in any way and they have 4 stools as a seating area that only work because they don't have the clientele to create a huge influx of customers. I'm more than astounded that this place has survived, it must be 20 years now and no one has moved in with a better product and service (though the new supermarket gives it a run for its money.)
